Boil 350ml of water in a #pot with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Pour the @Basmati Rice{1} into the #pot, turn the heat to its lowest setting and put a #lid on top. Leave the rice simmering on low heat for ~{10%minutes}, then rest off the heat for ~{10%minutes}.

> Do not lift the lid until 20 mins are up or your rice won't cook.

Peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled) in half lengthways. Slice the onion very thinly into half moons. Peel and very finely chop the @garlic{1%clove}(finely chopped). Chop the @Vine Tomatoes{2}(chopped into 2cm cubes). Chop the tops and bottoms from the @green beans{1/2}(chopped into 4).

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium low heat. Add your onions with @salt{1/4%tsp} and gently cook for ~{8%minutes}. For the last 2 mins add the @curry powder mix{1} and the garlic.

Turn the heat to medium. Add the @lamb mince{250} with @salt{pinch} and cook until it has browned off. Add @water{1/4%cup}, the green beans and tomatoes, place a #lid on the pan and cook on low for ~{6%minutes}.

Tip in your cooked rice and stir everything together.

Roughly chop @mint{3%tbsp} and @coriander{3%tbsp} and stir them through the biryani. Serve with a big dollop of @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{1} on top.

> If you have any spare fresh herbs, add them as well - the more the merrier!